<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  FIP - Big MT: Mutant & Pawn Condition Patches
  Rethemes Anomaly's pawn mutation states and humanoid entities.

  Shambler hediff / pawnkinds     → lobotomite
  Rising hediff                   → reactivating
  ShamblerCorpse hediff           → FEV subject corpse
  Ghoul hediff / pawnkind         → robobrain
  GhoulFrenzy hediff              → system overload
  Inhumanized hediff              → lobotomization
  Inhumanized codex (BlissLobotomy) kept as-is (already thematic)

  Note: The 'Shambler' and 'Inhumanized' pawn states remain mechanically distinct.
    - Lobotomites (Shamblers) are externally reanimated corpses directed by FEV aerosol
      or ZAX broadcast. They are dead.
    - Lobotomization (Inhumanized) is a living pawn condition — a pawn whose higher
      cognitive functions have been suppressed by prolonged Big MT broadcast exposure.
      They still breathe, still work, but they no longer feel connection to other humans.
-->
<Patch>

  <!-- ==================== SHAMBLER HEDIFF → LOBOTOMITE ==================== -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Shambler"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>lobotomite</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Shambler"]/description</xpath>
    <value><description>This individual's brain has been destroyed or removed, and their body is being animated by the Big MT broadcast signal and residual FEV activity. They retain basic motor function and aggressive targeting behavior, but no cognition, no social capacity, and no sense of pain. They will attack anything not broadcasting a Big MT recognition signal until their body fails.</description></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== RISING HEDIFF → REACTIVATING ==================== -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Rising"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>reactivating</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== SHAMBLER CORPSE HEDIFF ==================== -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="ShamblerCorpse"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>FEV subject corpse</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== SHAMBLER PAWNKINDS ==================== -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/PawnKindDef[defName="ShamblerSwarmer"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>lobotomite</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/PawnKindDef[defName="ShamblerSoldier"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>lobotomite soldier</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== SHAMBLER CODEX ENTRY ==================== -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/EntityCodexEntryDef[defName="Shambler"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>lobotomite</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/EntityCodexEntryDef[defName="Shambler"]/description</xpath>
    <value><description>Corpses or surgically brain-absent subjects reanimated by the Big MT broadcast signal and residual FEV activity. Lobotomites are slow, relentless, and mindless. They will continue attacking until their body reaches metabolic failure. Unlike true undead, they can theoretically be captured and studied — although what's left to study is largely mechanical.</description></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== GHOUL HEDIFF → ROBOBRAIN ==================== -->
  <!--
    Note: The Anomaly "Ghoul" is an archotech-shard-implanted human jittering murder machine.
    This is nothing like a Fallout ghoul. It maps better to a Robobrain — a brain fused with
    robot body that has gone haywire. The "shard" becomes the robot chassis control chip.
  -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Ghoul"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>robobrain implant</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Ghoul"]/description</xpath>
    <value><description>This person has had a Big MT neural override chip implanted in their brain stem — a device originally designed to turn a living subject into a remote-controlled weapon. The chip has gone haywire. It is sending constant high-frequency motor commands that the host cannot override, causing spasmodic, violent, and uncontrollable behavior. The host is still alive inside. They just can't stop.</description></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/PawnKindDef[defName="Ghoul"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>robobrain subject</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/EntityCodexEntryDef[defName="Ghoul"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>robobrain subject</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/EntityCodexEntryDef[defName="Ghoul"]/description</xpath>
    <value><description>A person implanted with a Big MT neural override chip. The chip has malfunctioned and is sending constant high-frequency commands the host cannot resist, turning them into a spasmodic killing machine. They remain biologically alive. They cannot be reasoned with while the chip is active.</description></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== GHOUL FRENZY → SYSTEM OVERLOAD ==================== -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="GhoulFrenzy"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>neural chip overload</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <!-- ==================== INHUMANIZED → LOBOTOMIZATION ==================== -->
  <!--
    The Inhumanized condition in Anomaly represents a pawn whose mind has been overwritten
    by the void's psychic patterns. In Big MT terms, this is a living pawn whose higher
    cognitive functions have been suppressed by prolonged Big MT broadcast exposure —
    a soft lobotomy delivered by signal. The pawn is still alive and functional, just
    disconnected from human emotional needs.
    
    This is mechanically distinct from the "lobotomite" (Shambler) which is a dead body
    being animated. This is a living person whose empathy and social cognition have been
    overridden by the broadcast. They can still work. They just don't care anymore.
  -->

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Inhumanized"]/label</xpath>
    <value><label>lobotomization</label></value>
  </Operation>

  <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
    <xpath>/Defs/HediffDef[defName="Inhumanized"]/description</xpath>
    <value><description>This person's higher cognitive functions have been suppressed by prolonged exposure to the Big MT broadcast signal. They retain full physical and intellectual capability — they can work, research, and fight — but their emotional responses, social needs, and empathetic capacity have been overwritten. They experience the world as a series of tasks without personal meaning.\n\nThey do not suffer. They are not sure what that means anymore.</description></value>
  </Operation>

</Patch>
